title: Grateful Dead Live at Madison Square Garden on 1982-09-20
lineage: Cassette Master (Sony TC-K677ES) -> Sound Devices 744T (24bit/48k) ->Adobe Audition v3.0 -> Samplitude Professional v11.2.1 -> FLAC/24
description:
Set 1

Shakedown Street-> Minglewood Blues, Candyman-> El Paso, Dupree's Diamond Blues, It's All Over Now, Good Time Blues, Row Jimmy, Throwing Stones-> Day Job

Set 2

Scarlet Begonias-> Fire On The Mountain, Women Are Smarter, Terrapin Station-> Drums-> Spanish Jam-> Truckin'-> The Other One-> Stella Blue-> Sugar Magnolia, E: Touch Of Gray

reviews.review_text:
It's always great at MSG This Garden show opened with a smokin’ Shakedown, 12 minutes of inspired Jerry, with some staggered vocals by Bobby and Brent.   Other first set highlights:  a crisp El Paso, the rare Dupree’s Diamond Blues, a nice tempo It’s All Over Now, and that lazy hazy Row Jimmy.

Second set:  the boys dive in with a big fat Scarlet/Fire.  The bridge had a moment of sloppiness, but otherwise pretty good.  Man Smart Woman Smarter has a nice intro. Standard Terrapin.  Solid back half second set with Truckin’, The Other One, a plaintive Stella Blue, and Sugar Mag.

The sound is pretty clean, with just the right crowd electricity you’d expect from an MSG  show.  Thanks to Frank Streeter and the legendary Charlie Miller for tape supply and edit work.  Well worth a download.
